# Governance Artifact Standards

## Patterns to Always Use
- Keep **DIRECTIVES.md** (repo root) **or** **HEXCURSE/DIRECTIVES.md** (install pack) in sync with Taskmaster `tasks.json` after each session close — use whichever path exists in **this** repo.
- Reference **docs/ARCHITECTURE.md** or **HEXCURSE/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md** for system truth; mark unknowns as `TBD — confirm before implementing`.
- Session start: follow **AGENTS.md** / **HEXCURSE/AGENTS.md** sequence exactly; session close: full checklist including MCP used/unused report per **mcp-usage.mdc** (see **docs/MCP_COORDINATION.md** or **HEXCURSE/docs/MCP_COORDINATION.md**).
- Continual learning: **RULE 9** / **agents-memory-updater** when triggers apply; classify merges per **docs/MEMORY_TAXONOMY.md** or **HEXCURSE/docs/MEMORY_TAXONOMY.md** — never raw transcript dumps into **AGENTS.md** (see **docs/CONTINUAL_LEARNING.md** or **HEXCURSE/docs/CONTINUAL_LEARNING.md**).

## Patterns to Never Use
- Marking more than one directive as In Progress in the active directives file.
- Omitting Taskmaster task IDs from in-progress directive blocks when tasks exist.

## File Naming Convention
- **Source-style repo (this project):** `AGENTS.md`, `DIRECTIVES.md`, `SESSION_LOG.md` at repo root; prompts under **`docs/`**.
- **Install-pack repo (other projects):** single **`HEXCURSE/`** tree — see **`HEXCURSE/PATHS.json`**.

## Testing Requirement
- None automated; verify manually that Taskmaster state matches the human-readable directives file when closing a session.

## Context7 Library IDs (add "use context7" when using these)
- Not applicable unless editing scripts that call external CLIs.
